It may be 12 years since I won my first national senior title, but some things haven’t changed - 
Soggy conditions ✅ 
National title retained ✅ 
Taking two hours to pee in a cup afterwards ✅

I was hoping to accept my invite to the World Championships this year but unfortunately a grade 2 calf strain in training this week has put paid to that. 
I’m no stranger to injury, but the timing of this one is pretty rotten. I live for and base my entire year around the major championships every summer, and having not missed a major championships since Tallinn 2011, I’m very disappointed. Training and racing had really started to click and I really felt it was all coming together but injury is always an occupational hazard. Yup, it’s unfortunate but it is what it is and we just have to keep on keeping on. If it were easy, everyone would be doing it. 
I may down but not out! These challenges make the successes all the more sweet, so let’s hope for a sweet 2024 🙏🏻. 
Thank you to everyone who has supported me this year, and also reached out with messages, it’s much appreciated!

Contrary to popular belief, I’m actually very happy with tonight’s race! Yup a 51 is my slowest time in a few years, but it wasn’t about the result.
A month ago, with a grade 2 calf tear, the goal posts were completely moved. World champs was out of the question but I needed a focus to make sure I set myself up well for 2024 and didn’t fall further onto the back foot. Having a race lined up kept me and my rehab on track. After only getting back into spikes again a week ago, the new goal was to get to the start line and finish healthy.
It’s not the season I wanted but for right now it’s mission accomplished, 2023 behind us, and looking forward to 2024. Thank you to everyone in my corner ❤️💪🏼 📸 @jrhodesathletics

I’m very excited and proud to be joining Ray Crofton Motors as a brand ambassador! I’m feeling very lucky to have taken delivery of my new Kia Sportage this morning. 

2024 is set to be a big year, and an important one. Having a brand new Kia under me gives me peace of mind to travel comfortably and reliably to training, events and competitions. I cannot thank the Crofton family, and everyone at @raycroftonmotors for (quite literally) supporting my athletic journey! #brandambassador
Winter training weekend ‘23 ✅
They say success doesn’t come from your comfort zone, but I’m feeling pretty comfy 🚘 (The hill training is a different story though…) #sp

I’m delighted to be part of the Team Ireland Dare To Believe initiative - Olympic Movement Breaks! It’s a series of recorded videos where I along with other elite athletes get to give a taster of our sport, that can be done in the classroom 📚. It’s a nice, short activity break from the books. The aim? To get more school children active 🤸‍♂️ which is something I truly believe in! I’m already hearing fantastic reports from teachers and students alike who have taken part, in running an Olympic Final with me!
Thumbs up for 2024! 👍🏼
